vulnerabilities.name: dependancy-without-cve
vulnerabilities.overview: pip 1.4 includes a security patch to pip's ssl support related to certificate DNS wildcard matching.
vulnerabilities.recommendation: Update dependancy-without-cve (1.3.0) to a non vulnerable version, vulnerable versions: <1.4

vulnerabilities.name: dependancy-with-cve
vulnerabilities.overview: The mirroring support (-M, --use-mirrors) in Python Pip before 1.5 uses insecure DNS querying and authenticity checks which allows attackers to perform man-in-the-middle attacks. See CVE-2013-5123.
vulnerabilities.recommendation: Update dependancy-with-cve (1.3.0) to a non vulnerable version, vulnerable versions: <1.5
